(1)
Cornelia Street, at the N.E. corner of Wilson Ave., showing the low frame annex building of P.S. No. 106, which also housed the Citizen's
Democratic Club. It was razed in June 1928.
January 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing P.S. No. 106 at the N.W. corner.
January 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
